  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Yupun breaks the 10 second barrier",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Yupun Abeykoon, the super sprint champion of Sri Lanka, managed to set a new South Asian and Sri Lankan record by finishing the 100m event in 9.96 seconds at the Reprint Athletics Championship in Switzerland.",
        "Thus, for the first time in the South Asian region, Yupun became the first player to complete the 100 meters event in less than 10 seconds.",
        "Yupun, who is showing the best performance of his career this year, managed to renew the 100m South Asian and Sri Lankan records on several occasions. Yupun's previous best time for 100 meters was 10.06 seconds.",
        "Jamaica's Usain Bolt holds the 100m world record with a time of 9.58 seconds."
      ],
